    {
      "id": "l4-separable-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Separable verbs and time",
      "body": "# Separable verbs\n\nMany German verbs have a **prefix** that splits off in a main clause and jumps to the **end**.\n\n> **aufstehen** → **Ich stehe** um sieben Uhr **auf.** — I get up at seven o'clock.\n> **anrufen** → **Ich rufe** meine Mutter **an.** — I call my mother.\n\nThe prefix often tells you the meaning, so learn the whole verb (*aufstehen*, *einkaufen*, *fernsehen*, *aufräumen*).\n\n## Telling the time\n\nUse **um** + number + **Uhr**:\n\n- **um sieben Uhr** — at seven o'clock\n- **um halb acht** — at half past seven (literally \"half eight\")\n\nParts of the day take **am**: *am Morgen*, *am Abend*."
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-ex-match-routine",
      "type": "exercise",
      "theory_ref": "l4-separable-theory",
      "title": "Match the daily-routine verbs",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l4-ex-match-routine",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each separable verb with its meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-a2-aufstehen", "de-a2-einkaufen", "de-a2-fernsehen", "de-a2-aufraeumen"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "aufstehen", "right": "to get up"},
          {"left": "einkaufen", "right": "to go shopping"},
          {"left": "fernsehen", "right": "to watch TV"},
          {"left": "aufräumen", "right": "to tidy up"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
